Questions:
What is the primary goal of the research study involving Xindilizumab for locally advanced head and neck tumors?
A) To compare the effectiveness of Xindilizumab with a placebo in improving hair growth; 
B) To assess the impact of Xindilizumab on the cognitive function of patients post-treatment; 
C) To evaluate the progression-free survival (PFS) and 1-year progression-free survival (PFS) in patients after radiotherapy and chemotherapy; 
D) To determine the best dietary practices for patients with head and neck tumors post-treatment.

Correct answer: C

If you choose not to participate in the Xindilizumab study for locally advanced head and neck tumors, what are the alternative options available to you?
A) You may seek alternative experimental treatments not described in this study; 
B) You can continue to receive treatment according to the standard diagnosis and treatment plan or participate in other studies; 
C) You will be required to undergo surgery instead of radiotherapy and chemotherapy; 
D) No alternative treatments are available outside of this study.

Correct answer: B

If you experience an adverse event or injury related to the study, whom should you contact for assistance and potential compensation?

A) The Human Research Ethics Committee of the Second Affiliated Hospital of Zhejiang University School of Medicine;
B) The principal investigator of the study;
C) The local pharmacy;
D) Your personal physician.

Correct answer: A) The Human Research Ethics Committee of the Second Affiliated Hospital of Zhejiang University School of Medicine;
